	<h2>About Randy Ingermanson</h2>
	<div class="floatRight"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100924160248im_/http://ingermanson.com/images/Randy150.jpg" alt="Randy Ingermanson" width="99" height="150"/></div>
	<p><strong>Randy earned</strong> a Ph.D. in physics at U.C. Berkeley and is the award-winning author of six novels and one non-fiction book. He writes about "The Intersection of Faith Avenue and Science Boulevard."</p>
	<p><strong>Randy publishes</strong> the world’s largest electronic magazine on the craft of writing fiction, the FREE monthly <strong><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100924160248/http://www.advancedfictionwriting.com/ezine" target="_blank">Advanced Fiction Writing E-zine.</a></strong> His ultimate goal is to become Supreme Dictator for Life and First Tiger and to achieve Total World Domination.</p> 
